lations have not produced isoleucine and that keto-acid routes remain unproven for this precursor.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_004\",\n        \"rxn_011\",\n        \"rxn_012\",\n        \"rxn_013\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Mark the entire alpha-keto-beta-methylvalerate branch as speculative and low-confidence.\",\n        \"Replace direct hydrothermal isoleucine formation claims with precursor-generation only.\",\n        \"Provide a more defensible nonenzymatic route to alpha-keto-beta-methylvalerate or remove this branch.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.55,\n        \"rxn_004\": 0.42,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.4,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.22,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.35\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.39,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.62,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.8,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.66,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.52,\n      \"feedback\": \"The UV amination concept is inspired by literature on ZnS photocatalytic amination of alpha-keto acids, but the network specifically uses TiO2-based surface chemistry rather than the more relevant ZnS system highlighted by the literature. More importantly, the precursor alpha-keto-beta-methylvalerate is not convincingly produced in the network. As a result, the final amination step is only loosely literature-aligned and the pathway remains speculative.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_004\",\n        \"rxn_011\",\n        \"rxn_012\",\n        \"rxn_014\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"If retaining photocatalytic amination, use ZnS-based conditions matching Wang et al. 2012 rather than generic TiO2.\",\n        \"Acknowledge that alpha-keto-beta-methylvalerate availability is the main unresolved bottleneck.\",\n        \"Downgrade this pathway to exploratory status.