y associated with enhanced branched alkyl amino acid formation (Parker et al., 2011; Ring et al., 1972; Pizzarello & Cronin, 2008). This is the core precursor-forming step for terrestrial isoleucine synthesis.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_009\",\n      \"name\": \"Meteorite parent-body delivery of 2-methylbutanal\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_005\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_011\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"sulfide minerals (stibnite/molybdenite)\", \"montmorillonite (clay)\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"parent-body inherited mineral organics delivered to surface pools\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"extraterrestrial infall and dissolution in surface aqueous reservoirs\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Exogenous delivery introduces preformed branched aldehydes from meteorite parent-body chemistry into terrestrial pools.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Pizzarello and Cronin (2008) provided isotopic evidence that the branched aldehyde precursor to isoleucine existed on meteorite parent bodies. This node supplies a second, literature-grounded route to the same hub molecule without forcing unsupported terrestrial synthesis details (Pizzarello & Cronin, 2008; Cronin et al., 1981).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_010\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker synthesis of isoleucine aminonitrile from 2-methylbutanal\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_011\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_004\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_012\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"montmorillonite (clay)\", \"sulfide minerals (stibnite/molybdenite)\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"300-370K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"mineral concentration surfaces\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"aqueous Strecker conditions after gas-phase discharge production of aldehy