 therefore this step is used only as network support (Springsteen et al., 2018; Barge et al., 2019)."}, {"id": "rxn_004", "name": "Surface spark-discharge production of HCN from reduced volcanic gases", "inputs": ["mol_003"], "outputs": ["mol_004"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["TiO2 (anatase/rutile)", "sulfide minerals (stibnite/molybdenite)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-370K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "TiO2 and sulfide mineral surfaces as collection/photochemical interfaces", "aqueous": "true", "other": "electrical discharge in CH4/NH3/CO2/H2S/H2O or CH4/N2/NH3/H2O atmospheres; volcanic lightning; anoxic"}, "mechanism": "Atmospheric discharge generates cyanide that is trapped into surface waters and mineral films.", "reasoning": "HCN is a core product of Miller-type discharge chemistry and the Strecker mechanism identified by Miller as the dominant amino acid-forming route; Parker et al. showed H2S-rich volcanic discharge conditions strongly expand amino acid diversity including isoleucine (Miller, 1957; Ring et al., 1972; Parker et al., 2011)."}, {"id": "rxn_005", "name": "Surface spark-discharge/radical formation of 2-methylbutanal", "inputs": ["mol_006", "mol_004"], "outputs": ["mol_007"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["TiO2 (anatase/rutile)", "sulfide minerals (stibnite/molybdenite)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "300-370K", "pressure": "1 atm", "catalyst": "TiO2 and sulfide mineral surfaces as radical/photochemical interfaces", "aqueous": "true", "other": "volcanic spark-discharge, H2S-enhanced radical chemistry; branched aldehydes formed in complex mixtures"}, "mechanism": "Electrical discharge and sulfur-radical chemistry generate branched hydrocarbon/aldehyde mixtures including 2-methylbutanal through radical recombination chemistry.", "reasoning": "The deep research identifies prebiotic generation of 2-methylbutanal as the key bottleneck and specifically points to radical chemistry in spark discharges, especially under H2S